Context: The Community Worker (C101) program is offered by George Brown College. To learn more about the program, register for an online information session by contacting Community Services at 416-415-5000, ext. 2185 or communityservices@georgebrown.ca, or email the Program Co-ordinator Farhia Abdi at fabdi7@georgebrown.ca. You can also watch a previously recorded session about the program. Application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours and more can be kept up-to-date by signing up on the website. Other contact information includes 416-415-2000 for general inquiries and TTY: 1-877-515-5559 for those with hearing impairments. For all other inquiries, email ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The information on the website is subject to change without notice. It should not be viewed as a representation, offer or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
